## Testing
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}
### Node.js
- Framework: Vitest
- Run all: `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} nx run-many --target=test`
- Run one: `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} nx test SERVICE_NAME`
- Watch: `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} nx test SERVICE_NAME --watch`
- Coverage: `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} nx test SERVICE_NAME --coverage`
{{ end }}
{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}
### Go
- Run all: `go test ./...`
- Run one: `go test ./apps/SERVICE_NAME/...`
- Race detection: `go test -race ./...`
- Coverage: `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...`
{{ end }}
### Testing Rules
- Unit tests live next to the code they test (`*.test.ts` / `*_test.go`)
- Integration tests hit real services (database, Redis) in the k3d cluster
- No mocking of infrastructure - test against real dependencies
- Every PR must pass CI tests before merge
